{
  "texts": [
    "In addition to this quantitative evaluation with the evaluation dataset, we also evaluate the performance of TacticAI's receiver prediction component in a case study with human raters.",
    "Please see the \"Case study with expert raters\" section for more details.",
    "For shot prediction, we observe that reusing the base TacticAI architecture to directly predict shot events-i.e., directly modelling the probability Pð shotjcorner Þ-proved challenging, only yielding a test F 1 score of 0.52 ± 0.03, for a GATv2 base model.",
    "Note that here we use the F 1 score-the harmonic mean of precision and recall-as it is commonly used in binary classification problems over imbalanced datasets, such as shot prediction.",
    "However, given that we already have a potent receiver predictor, we decided to use its output to give us additional insight into whether or not a shot had been taken."
  ]
}